- "crown jewel of the streaming world" refers to the top-rated movie;
- "stands atop the ratings mountain" refers to the movie with the highest average rating;
- "grace with its presence" refers to the number of streaming services the movie is available on.

- "Cinematic pearls" refer to the top-rated movies;
- "Shining the brightest in their respective genres" means the highest-ranked movies within each genre based on average user ratings;
- "Captivated the hearts of audiences" refers to having high average user ratings;
- "Achieved significant financial success" refers to the total revenue generated by the movies' respective genres.

- "runtime longer than 120 minutes" refers to movies that last more than 2 hours;
- "top 5 movies in each genre" are determined by the highest average user ratings;
- "jewels that shine the brightest" is a metaphor for the most highly rated movies.

- "Top-rated movies" refers to movies with the highest average ratings, divided into quartiles;
- "Genres" are the categories or types of movies, such as action, drama, or comedy;
- "Streaming services" are platforms where movies are available for viewing online.

- "Shining star" refers to the genre with the highest average rating;
- "New millennium" refers to movies released after the year 2010;
- "More than a handful of reviews" refers to movies with more than 5 ratings.
